reviews.author_name: London Flareon Tokyo Ebisu - Swanslade 恵比寿-スワンズレイド
reviews.text: West Byfleet is is located in the town with the same name and is served by Southwest Trains. Whilst being fairly close to Woking, this station is convenient and used by commuters and travellers alike, the station is a great place to go trainspoting. The area is an excellent place to hang out on a weekend as a side note.
Good links to London. Small station. Good carpark.

The station car park seems to be quite busy and full a lot of the time. However the station is located in a fairly decent location. 4 trains per hour in each direction serve here but peak trains can be disgustingly overcrowded. Lifts are available here as well as a grimy subway linking the platforms but the step up to trains on Platform 3 is almost as bad as Weybridge. It's way too high.
A nice place to go at the weekend, but the trains spoil it.
